Reach for the Top / 97Read and EnjoyRead and EnjoyRead and EnjoyRead and EnjoyRead and EnjoyTreesreesreesreesreesI think that I shall never seeA poem lovely as a tree.
A tree whose hungry mouth is prestAgainst the earth’s sweet flowing breast;
A tree that looks at God all dayAnd lifts her leafy arms to pray;
A tree that may in summer wearA nest of robins in her hair;
Upon whose bosom snow has lain;
Who intimately lives with rain.
Poems are made by fools like me,
But only God can make a tree.
JOYCE KILMERWhen eating fruit, think of the person whoplanted the tree.
